<article class="row content-row">
	<div class="col-sm-4">
		<h3 class="content-h">What’s new in version 2</h3>

		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-sm-10">
				In this release we’ve re-built the GUI from the ground up. After much deliberation and collaboration with internal tech teams we decided to move
				away from Bootstrap and create leaner, more semantic and modular code that’s tailored to our needs. Kudos to the awesome Bootstrap framework for
				getting us this far.
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="col-sm-8 index-section">
		<div class="index-block">
			<ul class="lists lists-neutral">
				<li>
					We&rsquo;ve simplified the GUI navigation structure making it easier to find the elements you need. We&rsquo;ve also added more intent around the
					use of each element.
				</li>
				<li>
					We&rsquo;ve re-built all the components for better accessibility, more semantic code, built in print stylesheets and a dynamic versioning system.
				</li>
				<li>
					To minimise code we&rsquo;ve added a new feature called the Blender. Now you can choose the elements you need and leave the ones you don&rsquo;t.
					Elements are grouped into self contained modules. This allows us to version each module rather than the entire GUI making it much easier to update
					your project. You can always access earlier versions.
				</li>
				<li>
					As well as providing the HTML markup for each element in the GUI you now also get CSS, LESS and JavaScript files with your GUI download.
				</li>
				<li>
					We&rsquo;ve added some new elements and classes like tabcordions which are responsive tab sets that change into accordions when viewed on small
					devices.
				</li>
				<li>
					We&rsquo;ve been through more rounds of rigorous accessibility testing to ensure every element is AA compliant both code and visual.
				</li>
				<li>
					We&rsquo;ve removed the icon font and replaced it with an SVG solution which is more optimised, semantic and accessible.
				</li>
				<li>
					Also, to encourage collaboration the GUI is now open source.
				</li>
			</ul>

			<p>
				Thanks to everyone for your help and support, we hope you like it. Please let us know if you have any feedback.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</article>


